Server side:
import socket

server = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)
server.bind(("localhost", 9999))
server.listen(1)

print("TCP Server is waiting for connection...")
conn, addr = server.accept()
print("Connected with:", addr)

data = conn.recv(1024).decode()
print("Client:", data)

conn.send("Message received via TCP".encode())
conn.close()
output:
TCP Server is waiting for connection...
Connected with: ('127.0.0.1', 50125)
Client: Hello Server, this is TCP Client


client side:
import socket

client = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)
client.connect(("localhost", 9999))

client.send("Hello Server, this is TCP Client".encode())
print(client.recv(1024).decode())

client.close()
output:Message received via TCP


